Reasoning: The paper deals with information retrieval and natural language processing tasks such as named entity recognition, relationship extraction, and topic modeling. These tasks are typically associated with the sub-categories of Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computation and Language (cs.CL), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper also mentions data mining and visualization goals, which are relevant to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses the experimental test bed for event mapping, which involves tracking events across time and space, and this is related to the sub-category of Digital Libraries (cs.DL).
